\section{Overview}

\begin{itemize}
\item {\bf Source Verse} is (an approximation of) the full source language.
\item The \emph{superficial-desugar} pass desugars Source Verse into {\bf Essential Verse},
  whose distinctive feature is TimLambdas.  Essential Verse is a subset of Source Verse.
\item We have three different approaches to the denotational semantics of Essential Source Verse:
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Plan A: a direct denotational semantics.
  \item Plan B: desugar into {\bf Destination Passing Style Verse} (DPS Verse), then give a semantics to that.
  \item Plan C: desugar into {\bf Mini Verse}, still in expression style, and give a semantics to that.
  \item Plan D: (older) desguar into {\bf ICFP Verse}, whose lambdas are simpler.
  \end{itemize}

